<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-30T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-30T15:00:00-05:00" n="1148" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1148">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">867.512/219: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-30T22:00:00+02:00">January
                                    30, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received January 31—8:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>196. Department’s 94, January 29, 5 p.m. I perceive no objection to the
                            Department recommending to the Department of Commerce the issuance of a
                            statement to American exporters to the effect that the Turkish
                            Government is prepared to guarantee payment to American exporters for
                            exports to Turkey which Turkish merchants are unable to pay for on
                            account of the capital tax.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>